message.content: We refer to Wikipedia articles on medicine for help. The abnormal vaginal bleeding and the elevated beta-HCG and AFP levels suggest an ovarian tumor that produces both hormones. Among the options, only Embryonal carcinoma is a type of germ cell tumor that can produce both hormones. Corpus luteum cyst produces progesterone, Krukenberg tumor is a metastatic tumor, and Serous cystadenoma is a cystic tumor that doesn't produce hormones.
